<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-10-19T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-10-19T09:00:00-05:00" n="488" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d488">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Tri-Motors Safety
                                Airways/146: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gordon</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-10-19T14:00:00+00:00">October 19, 1929—2
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 19—10:20
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>483. Reference Department’s telegram 316, October 1, 6 p.m. Orally
                                informed by Ministry for Foreign Affairs as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“Authorization accorded for two months provided that during
                                        that period there shall be concluded an accord looking to
                                        cooperation between French Aéropostale and the New York,
                                        Rio, and Buenos Aires Lines and the Pan American Airways.
                                        Further the New York, Rio, Buenos Aires planes not to carry
                                        photographic apparatus nor to fly over zone of Fort de
                                        France.”</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gordon</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>